Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the onion and garlic and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @butternut squash{1}(diced) and fry for ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add the @paprika{1%sachet} and @vegetable stock{1%sachet} along with @water{to taste} (about 500ml). Bring to the boil and simmer until veg is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Add half the @creme fraiche{62.5%g} (double for 4p) and blend until smooth with a #hand blender{}. Allow to warm through, then season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

When the soup has ~{5%minutes} of cooking time left, crumble the @blue cheese{55%g} and sprinkle it evenly over the @flatbread{2}.

Pop the flatbreads onto a lined #baking tray{} and warm in your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Allow the flatbreads to rest outside the oven for ~{1-2%minutes} then cut into even slices.

> TIP: If you're not a fan of blue cheese feel free to give it a miss!

Divide the velvety butternut squash soup between bowls.

Serve the flatbread slices alongside with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.